•	Customer Experience (Expectation with [Network] experts):

•	Having an amazing Customer experience is core responsibility for the support team.

•	When the support case is going back and forth with customer and support, it causes dissatisfaction. Frame your questions in such a way that you get all the information you need before you can propose a solution to the customer. 

•	Handling [Network] tickets: 
  
•	Always avoid offering incorrect advice. When in doubt or unsure of the answer and other relevant procedures, it's better to reroute the case to T2 or leave it for an expert that actually knows the answer rather than provide incomplete/risky or misleading information.


•	When you provide an answer to the customer, share the KBA or the help portal links as well. Suggestion: If the solution or workaround needs a SYSTEM CHANGE, such as deleting an item or changing a setting, you should refer to a document. If the solution does not lead to a system change, like refreshing or creating a new entry, referring to a document is optional.


•	It's Mandatory for experts to verify KBAs/HP documentation before sharing solutions and experts must not share or refer to any non-HP site while offering solutions to customers.

•	Experts should only use HP Approved mode of Inbound and outbound communication with HP Customers (Email, SoMe Chats and HP Cloud/Avaya Telephony).


•	Experts should NOT support other HP products under the wrong component. If an incident is incorrectly created in a particular HP product but pertains to another HP product, experts should ensure it is rerouted to HP for proper handling.

•	Experts should not provide an irrelevant or excessive text that does not address the customer's concern. Responses should be concise, clear, and directly related to the issue. If further clarification is needed, break down the steps in an easy-to-follow manner.

•	Experts must understand when to pursue further and reroute/move the case back to HP. If you see the need to continuously ask for screenshots to understand the customer’s setup, it advised you move the case back to HP with the reroute code “Additional Support required from T2” 

E.g. If you have already had 5 interactions, it is high indicator that this case would need to be accessed by HP to further assist the customer.

•	Don't give advice on issues outside of the product area of the ticket - Reroute instead to next level of support. 

•	Experts should not download customer data and save information on their desktops. Experts should promote a clean desk policy and paperless environment. Both at B&M and WFH.  

If required remind the customer to avoid sharing credentials, logs, or other sensitive information while seeking advice.

•	Lastly, Experts should not advise customers to upload the images/screenshots to any third-party services (imgbb.com, Google Drive, One Drive, https://paste.pics/, etc.) for Privacy and Security reasons. Customers might upload images with PII on them. Instead, you can ask the customers to copy and paste the error message or code in the chat, or to describe the issue as best as they can.
 
