4. URGENTLY Reroute: How to Handle Urgent or High-Priority Issues?
•	System Down or Critical Errors: Any case marked as an urgent issue, where the system is down or severely impacted, must be routed to HP immediately with clear documentation and escalation flags.

•	Tickets related to log, Credential, HP warranty, HP partners, HP system access, HP subscriptions check, cases requiring internal HP queues, cases requires advanced debugging [e.g., syntax errors, HP note issues], and If a response provides incorrect or harmful information that could potentially damage the system [e.g., critical configurations], immediately route the case to HP.

•	If a case comes through in a language other than English, reroute immediately.
•	Please reroute any questions with a mention of "Russia" or "Belarus."

•	Choosing the correct reroute code
o	Ensure to use the right reroute code when moving a case back to HP.
o	The system access required should be used when you see the need to access the customer’s system in order to further troubleshoot the issue.
o	HP Action required to be used when to further assist the customer HP support would need to work with internal teams. 

•	Cases or tickets where customers request HP experts in the following scenarios need to be immediately rerouted to Tier 2 experts.
o	When documentation needs to be updated
o	The current issue references other cases for context, or customer asks for a specific HP person.
o	Customer raises a license or contractual Issues: In cases where the license or contractual details need checking or clarification, please reroute to the HP Tier 2.
o	If the customer asks to modify, delete, or edit database or table data.

•	Urgently Rerouting Process Violations:
o	Do not attempt unnecessary troubleshooting steps when rerouting is required or mentioned in the HP Expert guidelines.


o	Avoid delaying rerouting or rerouting without informing the customer, as this can cause user frustration, we always recommend experts to inform customers before rerouting and to use the approved Rerouting template:

